{"descriptions":[{"id":357,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp\u003eExamples: ཆེ་, ཆུང་, རིང་, དཀར་\u003c/p\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":false,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:07:36 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:07:36 UTC","authors":[{"id":"2","fullname":"David Germano"}]},{"id":358,"title":null,"content":"\u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eAdjectives can be thought of as having \u0026ldquo;short\u0026rdquo; and \u0026ldquo;long\u0026rdquo; forms. The short form of an adjective is an adjective\u0026rsquo;s monosyllabic root; this short form hardly ever appears alone.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eFor example, the short form of \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགསར་པ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;new\u0026rdquo; would be \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eགསར་\u003c/span\u003e; the short form of \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམངར་མོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;sweet\u0026rdquo; would be \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམངར་\u003c/span\u003e; the short form of \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམང་པོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;many\u0026rdquo; would be \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eམང་\u003c/span\u003e, and so forth. An important exception to this rule is the adjective \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆེན་པོ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;big,\u0026rdquo; of which the short form is \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆེ་\u003c/span\u003e and not \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆེན་\u003c/span\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e \u003cp class=\"Paragraph\"\u003eAll adjectival suffixes are attached to the short form of the adjective. For example, the adjective \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུང་ཆུང་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;small\u0026rdquo; can be reduced to its short form \u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུང་\u003c/span\u003e; adjectival suffixes can then be attached to this single syllable to produce:\u003c/p\u003e \u003cul\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུང་བ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Smaller\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུང་དྲགས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;Too small\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུང་ལོས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;How small?\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུང་ཤོས་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;The smallest\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུང་ཙམ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;A bit small\u0026rdquo; \u003c/li\u003e \u003cli\u003e\u003cspan class=\"tibetan\" title=\"Type ID here\"\u003eཆུང་བ་ལ་\u003c/span\u003e \u0026ldquo;How small!\u0026rdquo;\u003c/li\u003e \u003c/ul\u003e","source_url":null,"is_primary":true,"created_at":"2013-09-15 04:07:36 UTC","updated_at":"2013-09-15 04:07:36 UTC","authors":[{"id":"6","fullname":"Nicolas Tournadre"}]}]}